(267, '2010-09-24 22:04:36', '2010-09-24 22:04:36', 589, 'Lee''s Sandwiches', 'lee-s-sandwiches', NULL, '<p><span style="color: #996600;">Lee&rsquo;s Sandwiches is the product of the merging of ideas and family support. Chieu Le, the founder, came to America and settled in San Jose, CA in 1980. He began taking adult education classes to study English and frequently bought food from a catering truck before and after class. Seeing the potential of a portable food service vehicle, Chieu Le worked on a catering truck to better understand the business. By 1981, he bought his first catering truck and started his route around San Jose.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #996600;">Chieu Le saw more potential in the catering truck business. He saw the need for trucks to have a place to park and clean their trucks with access to easily restock food and ice. The idea developed into Lee Bros. Foodservices, Inc, which him and his younger brother Henry Le developed in 1982. They chose the name &ldquo;Lee&rdquo; so it would be easily pronounced. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #996600;">Within time, they created the largest industrial catering company in Northern California; serving more than 500 independently owned and operating catering trucks at one time. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #996600;">In 1983, Chieu&rsquo;s parents, Ba Le  and Hanh Nguyen, started serving <em>banh mi</em>, Vietnamese style sandwiches from their catering truck by San Jose State University to the students and residents in the area. It became an instant hit among the community. Wanting to create a more permanent location and expand the options for their patrons, they opened the first Lee&rsquo;s Sandwiches location on Santa Clara Street. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #996600;">In 2001, Chieu Le and his eldest  son, <strong>Minh Le</strong>, developed a new concept of Lee&rsquo;s Sandwiches. In addition to the  traditional Vietnamese <em>banh mi</em> sandwiches, they added Euro-style sandwiches, fresh baked baguettes and croissants, an extensive line of drinks including the Lee&rsquo;s Coffee &ndash; <em>ca phe sua da</em> and desserts. The family came together and developed this new concept and opened the first store in Southern California on Bolsa Avenue in Westminster, CA.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #996600;">The success of the new concept was profound and well received by the community. Unfortunately, Minh was not able to see his dream come to life. Minh passed away on March 29, 2001, at age 21. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #996600;">However, the dream lives on, within a few short years, Lee&rsquo;s Sandwiches grew rapidly, locations opening in Northern California and Southern California then onto Arizona, Texas and Oklahoma. Currently there are over three-dozen stores, with plans to expand across the country. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #996600;">Lee&rsquo;s Sandwiches attracts a diverse crowd, from traditional Vietnamese- Americans to a younger crowd, all ethnicities of all ages with the extensive menu that offers a unique dining experience for every preference. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #996600;">Beyond providing fresh and delicious food for their customers, Lee&rsquo;s Sandwiches is heavily involved with the communities it serves. They have contributed and helped raised additional funds for many tragedies including 9-11, Hurricane Katrina, the floods in Vietnam, earthquakes in Mexico, and other local charities such as donating food and sponsoring various community and non profit events. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #996600;">Lee&rsquo;s Sandwiches epitomizes their role as a community leader and sets the example of embracing their responsibility of contributing for the better of the community. </span></p>', NULL, 10.00, 1.00, 0, '2010-09-24 22:06:51', '2010-09-26 18:30:00', 90.00, 9.00, 9.00, 20, NULL, 42658, 56, '<p>If you''re coming to this Lee''s Sandwiches shop, better drive up in a beat up car! &nbsp;Parking here is horrendous and tight! &nbsp;My car did not get hit but I saw a few instances where other cars in the parking came pretty damn close!<br /><br />Lee''s Sandwiches is a Vietnamese sandwich shop and market. &nbsp;Most of the stuff it sells are packaged sandwiches and sweets. &nbsp;There is a section of the small store that prepares made to order sandwiches. &nbsp;I came here to buy some Vietnamese sandwiches for the road. &nbsp;The prices are reasonable ranging from $2.50 to $3.00 per 12-inch sandwich. &nbsp;I tried two sandwiches and they were pretty good. &nbsp;The French bagguette bread was not rock hard and the sandwich fillings are pretty tasty. &nbsp;My favorite is the roasted pork with jalapenos.<br /><br />Aside from made to order sandwiches, come with someone who''s fluent in the Vietnamese language. &nbsp;I have a feeling that most workers don''t speak/understand English. &nbsp;<br /><br />Lee''s lost one star for this: &nbsp;I was paying for my food and a worker purposely bumped me aside so she can stack and organized pre-packaged foods on the counter. &nbsp;Not even a "excuse me" or anything. &nbsp;That instantly angered</p>', 1, 0, 1, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2010-09-29 18:30:00', '<ul>\r\n<li>Expires in 1 year</li>\r\n<li>Limit 1 per person, may buy 2 additional as gifts. By appointment only. Not valid for Gold Collagen facial. Valid only at listed location. No cash back. Gratuity not included. Not valid with other offers.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>* the foods are excellent</p>\r\n<p>* buy organic yogurt</p>\r\n<p>* share with your friends</p>', '<p>The facial treatments at herbal MINERAL will make you feel like you''ve got a brand new face without undergoing the experimental face-swapping surgery that''s still illegal in a plurality of states. Here''s a guide to determining if you are really in need of surgical face replacement:</p>\r\n<p><em>You Have Facial Scars</em><br /> <strong>Do You 