hanks Frugal Girls, for really keeping me afloat and happy on a budget!” ~ Desiree\n\n    * “Frugal Girls, THANK YOU for the tips, links, coupons, craft ideas, etc. You Rock!” ~ Lisa\n\n    * Frugal Girls ~ you have the BEST deals!  Thank you!!!!  ~ Arianne\n\n    * Thank you for all of the Free stuff!  You make a stay-at-home mother’s job fun and easy!  ~ Stephanie\n\n    * I’m new at couponing but it didn’t take long to get addicted.  Your website\n      is fun, perky and really helpful.  Thanks!  ~ Elizabeth\n\nMore Random Facts About Me…\n\n    * First and foremost, I’m a follower of God.\n    * I just can’t imagine life without Jesus by my side!\n    * I’m oh-so grateful for all the wonderful blessings he sends our way each day.\n    * I was born in Washington.\n    * Washington State that is {not D.C.}\n    * The western part.\n\n    * Know what that means?\n    * Yup… that means rain.\n\n    * Lots and lots of rain.\n    * If you’re not from the NW, you have no idea how much rain I’m talking!\n    * I met my hubby when we were in college.\n    * We were 19 years old.\n    * We went to two different colleges, but met at church.\n    * For awhile, I thought his name was Travis.\n    * Later I found out it wasn’t.\n    * I knew I had to get to know him from the moment he walked through the door.\n    * Aww ~ love at first glimpse?\n    * He took me to Phantom of the Opera for one of our first dates.\n    * It was downtown… in Seattle.\n    * I got a dozen beautiful roses that night.\n\n    * I got another dozen the next night!\n    * He’s still had a hard time topping that. ;)\n    * We dated for 2.5 years before getting married.\n    * That was way too long.', NULL, 100.00, 98.00, 0, '2011-01-08 18:30:00', '2011-01-24 18:30:00', 2.00, 2.00, 2.00, 2, 4, 42550, 56, '', 2, 0, 2, 2, '2011-01-17 11:01:59', '2011-01-09 18:30:00', '2011-01-26 18:30:00', '', '', '', 1, 1, 0, 5, 0.00, 2.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '', '', 'http://bit.ly/fVMUc0', 'http://bit.ly/elkHmt'),
