(751, '2011-01-16 09:11:13', '2011-01-17 19:03:07', 1, 'Sydney Harbour Bridge Climb Experience', 'sydney-harbour-bridge-climb-experience-1', NULL, 'BridgeClimb opened its doors in The Rocks, Sydney, on 1 October 1998, providing public access to the catwalks and ladders of the Sydney Harbour Bridge for the very first time. Since then we have opened a variety of Climbs that operate from dawn through to night, led by our dedicated team of Climb Leaders.\r\n\r\nIn October 2009 BridgeClimb launched its new Climber Base and a new Climb experience, The Express Climb - ideal for people who are short of time but still wish to experience The Climb of Their Life!\r\n\r\nSince our inception, we have assisted over two million locals and international visitors climb to the summit of the Sydney Harbour Bridge, 134 metres above the city’s beautiful harbour. They include many celebrities, and our 100-year-old Climber, Mrs. Chris Muller. We have donated over $4.5million worth of Climbs to charities, schools and other organisations and made over 2500 ', 'Rip off', 250.00, 50.00, 0, '2011-01-16 11:00:00', '2011-01-24 07:00:00', 80.00, 200.00, 200.00, 3, 200, 0, 173, 'Nathaniel Ballance from USA said:\r\nClimbing the Sydney Harbor Bridge was one of the most memorable experiences I had in Australia. Every once and a while during my travels, I have a "Wow, I''m actually here" moment and the Bridge Climb was one of them. The breathtaking view of the harbor and the city of Sydney from the top was worth every step it took to get there. It''s an experience that I will never forget and one that I hope one day to have again.', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2011-01-18 03:00:00', '2011-01-26 03:00:00', '* Use Fast\r\n* Don''t Faint', '* You will be High\r\n* OMG Don''t Fall', 'In lieu of typical product sales, WigWon Inc occasionally offers a blind grab bag officially called "Random Crap." While today its accompanying picture of a paper pony', 0, 1, 1, 2, 0.00, 50.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '