(756, '2011-01-17 10:38:12', '2011-01-17 10:38:12', 1403, '$25 for $50 Worth of Upscale Cuisine and Drinks at Braise Food & Wine', '$25-for-$50-worth-of-upscale-cuisine-and-drinks-at-braise-food-wine', NULL, '\n\nBefore the mainstreaming of haute cuisine, quality dining was once a privilege only for friends of professional chefs, their mothers, and the lucky silverware. Today''s Groupon gives discerning palates a taste of the good stuff: for $25, you get $50 worth of upscale cuisine and drinks at Braise Food & Wine in central London. Nestled in the newly renovated Hotel Metro, Braise concocts thoughtful seasonal dishes with fresh and natural ingredients against a backdrop of warm, casual elegance. Mouths scheme to become one with the menu''s bison carpaccio ($13) before taking in the essences of the dry-aged rib eye with creamy bone marrow, vegetables, and sauce bordelaise ($35), all pairable with a choice from Braise''s wine regiment, which checks in at more than 500 members strong. Diners of the herbivorous persuasion can coddle the six-course vegetarian tasting menu ($75) in their bellies as a prelude to the signature made-to-order donuts, filled with the uncompromising nectars of sweet-potato maple, strawberry-rhubarb jam, chocolate, and buttermilk.', NULL, 50.00, 25.00, 0, '2011-01-18 07:00:00', '2011-01-21 06:00:00', 50.00, 25.00, 25.00, 5, NULL, 0, 175, 'I can''t recommend this restaurant enough. If you enjoy food you''ll enjoy the flavours, atmosphere and friendly staff at Braise. – AmyP', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2011-01-25 07:00:00', '2011-01-27 07:00:00', 'Pick a Theme: For boys, fire-truck-themed parties are fun and inexpensive—simply order some fire trucks by calling 911 and demanding that the professionals come to your house and set something on fire—it''s your right as a taxpayer. For girls, princess-themed parties can give your little ones the unrealistic expectations of privilege and romance they''ll need to succeed in the real world.'