(759, '2011-01-17 18:11:15', '2011-01-18 16:50:49', 1409, '$5 for $10 Worth of Beef Sandwiches, Burgers, and More at Zippy''s', '$5-for-$10-worth-of-beef-sandwiches,-burgers,-and-more-at-zippy-s', NULL, '"Fast food" refers to an advanced method of quickly preparing and delivering edibles, but according to Kroc''s Law, its pace will accelerate until the populace must spend mealtime dodging supersonic burgers. Enjoy the more manageable gait of modern fare with today''s Groupon: for $5, you get $10 worth of food and drink at Zippy''s, with locations in Schaumburg and Hoffman Estates. Zippy''s serves up a menu of burgers ($3.49–$4.35), wraps ($5.45–$6.25), gyros ($2.09–$6.19), and more, with a slate of sippable malts ($2.79–$4.20) and milkshakes offering decadent dairydom ($2.13–$3.54). Lovingly inhale one of Zippy''s signature, mozzarella-drenched Cheezy Beef sandwiches with a garlic bread-bookended version available for those seeking to ward off vampire telemarketers ($3.35–$6.29). Zippy''s also offers a dollar menu containing mini-meal options for Lilliputian appetites.', '', 10.00, 5.00, 0, '2011-01-17 18:13:00', '2011-01-21 03:00:00', 50.00, 5.00, 5.00, 20, 1000, 0, 177, 'Yelpers give the Hoffman Estates location and the Schamburg location a 3.5-star average:\n\n        * If you dig gyros theirs are delicious and they even have a killer chicken gyro. – Justin W.\n        * This is my favorite slice of pizza in the northwest suburbs. – Sean R.\n', 3, 0, 1, 5, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2011-02-01 03:00:00', '2011-02-28 03:00:00', 'Expires 2012-05-01 12:00:00 AM\n\n    * Expires Jul 17, 2011\n    * Limit 3 per person. Limit 1 per order. Valid only at listed locations. Must use in 1 visit, no cash back. Tax not included. Not valid with other offers.\n    * See the rules that apply to all deals.\n\nRead the Deal FAQ for the basics.', '    * Famous Cheezy Beef sandwiches\n    * Burgers, pitas & more\n    * Dollar menu\n', 'Run Quickly: Most participants simply stand in one place hoping the bulls will gore them with their lucky horns, but bulls love a challenge. To increase your chances of being mauled by a bull''s gold-filled horns, run wildly while dressed like the bulls'' natural prey: an elephant. Using roller skates to increase your speed is considered cheating unless the bulls are also wearing them.\n\nAvoid the Color Red: Bulls, like donkeys and children, are sterile. The romantic color enrages them because it reminds them that they are unable to mate with one another. Avoid other popular colors such as blue or yellow (or any combination of blue, yellow, and red), because bulls are colorblind and will mistake these hues for the hated red.\n\nEmbrace the Bull Within: Spain''s most successful matadors don''t defeat their bulls using swords, larger swords, or a series of large swords—they defeat them using the "sword" of empathy and then finish them off with nonmetaphorical swords just for show. Sharpen your blade by pondering the same question the bulls face every day: "Where am I?"', 0, 1, 0, 2, 0.00, 50.00, 0.00, 0.00, 0.00, '', '', 'http://bit.ly/dZz5yu', 'http://bit.ly/fOT25U'),
